6 Ways to Get Out of Stress in One Minute
Too few of us can afford to run a weekend to the mountains to relieve stress.
Some take our time, others our finances, and others both.
But there are solutions available to anyone who wants to relieve a little stress.
They did not involve any high costs or special time allocated, according to lyla.ro.
Everyday worries are inevitable, but it's up to us how we deal with them and what attitude we take towards them.
Instead of grinding you inside and feeling an implosion taking place in your mind, you better try the following relaxation tactics that won't steal more than a minute.
Take a deep breath.
Breathing exercises are not just intended for soloists or yoga practitioners.
They work for any individual, and regulating breathing at a tense moment helps release endorphins into the body, which leads to a state of relaxation, informs Livestrong.
Be a child.
We know we're over our childhood age and we can't afford to pet each other when we feel like it.
But that doesn't mean we can't go to a corner of office headquarters or wherever we know we're alone (even behind the building) and not scream while our lungs are holding.
You can get rid of the nerves and the negative energy accumulated over the course of a day with a few big screams.
Imagine a beautiful place.
We know the recommendation sounds worthy of a replica from a psychotherapy session, but not for nothing psychologists often use it.
Imagination of a beautiful place, which inspires us calmly and detached from daily frenzy, can lead to alleviation of the state of nerves.
It is, indeed, self-suggestion, a process that can actually change lives, both for the better and for the worse.
It all depends on what we're suggesting.
It is best to think of an idyllic place that warms our soul.
Listen to the music
Put your headphones in your ears and listen to the relaxing music.
Attention, this is not about your favorite music, because if it is about heavy metal you may encounter difficulties in relaxing.
Listen to even relaxing songs, which are smooth and do not contain lyrics, to find your balance when your fuse is lit.
Peel an orange
Does the advice to peel an orange to the nerves sound strange?
Well, it's not!
Because it is not the fruit itself, because it does not contain miraculous substances or Xanax to disconnect us completely (occasional, too total).
It's about aromatherapy!
The smell of the orange peel, during peeling, stimulates the brain to produce endorphins, hormone of the state of well-being.
He caresses an animal.
Those who have animals close by, whether it's the one at home, or it's the one who came around the workplace, take a few seconds to caress him.
According to the U.S. National Center for Infectious Diseases, petting animals can lower blood pressure.
