While I wrote the article, it occurred to me to check the story of the former warrior and "Syrian rebel commander Laith Al-Saleh" in the second part of the space dedicated by V. Marin to his person "jihadist Laith Al-Saleh" (the two categorisations - "rebel" and "jihadist" - could in itself make me a circumspect start).
I didn't.
