Winner in the Iaş Rally, Simone Tempestini secured his national title at the rally, becoming the youngest winner in the history of the championship
The rally of Iasi Cotnari 2015 ended with a fabulous result of the young pilot Simone Tempestini, Italian with Romanian citizenship, who won all nine special challenges of the most difficult stage of the National Rally Championship at 21.
As a leader in the competition until now, Simone became a pre-final stage national champion, with co-pilot Dorin Pulpea on a Ford Fiesta R5.
Tempestini juniori became the youngest Romanian rally champion, the previous recordman, from 2011, belonging to Valentin Porcisteanu (28 years and nine months).
In the seven stages of the National Dunlop Rally Championship, Simone won 47 special challenges, and the performance from Iași re-edits the previous one in the Arad Rally.
